olive oil
½ Onion
2 clove garlic
1 packet red lentils
1 packet Peeled Prawns
20 g butter
1 sachet Mumbai Spice Blend
1 packet Bengal Curry Paste
1 packet tomato paste
2 cup water
½ tsp salt
1 packet Coconut Milk
1 Carrot
1 packet Green beans
pinch Chilli Flakes
6 Mini Flour Tortillas
1 packet Baby Leaves
½ packet Greek-Style Yoghurt
1 packet Coriander

• Finely chop onion (see ingredients) and garlic. Rinse half the red lentils.

• In a large deep frying pan (or saucepan), heat a drizzle of olive oil over medium-high heat. Cook prawns, tossing, until pink and starting to curl up, 3-4 minutes. Transfer to a bowl.
• Return pan to medium high heat with the butter and a drizzle of olive oil. Cook onion, stirring, until
softened, 3-4 minutes.
• Add garlic and Mumbai spice blend and cook until fragrant, 1 minute.
• Add a drizzle of olive oil, then add Bengal curry paste and tomato paste and cook, stirring, until fragrant, 2 minutes.

• Add the water, the salt, lentils and coconut milk to the pan. Stir well to combine. Cover with a lid, reduce the heat to medium and cook until the lentils have softened, 20-25 minutes.
• While the lentils are cooking, grate carrot. Trim and halve green beans.
• In the last 5 minutes of cook time, remove the lid and stir through the carrot and green beans. Cook until softened.

TIP: Add a splash of water if the dhal looks dry.

• While the dhal is cooking, heat a medium frying pan over medium-high heat with the olive oil (21/2 tbs for 2 people / 1/3 cup for 4 people). Add a pinch of chilli flakes (if using) and cook until fragrant, 1 minute.
• Transfer chilli-infused oil to a small bowl. Brush (or spread using the back of a spoon) some chilli oil over both sides of a mini flour tortilla.
• Return frying pan to medium-high heat, then cook the tortilla until golden, 1 minute each side. Transfer to a paper towel-lined plate.
• Repeat with remaining chilli oil and tortillas.

• When the dhal has finished cooking, stir through cooked prawns and baby spinach leaves until wilted. Season with salt and pepper.

TIP: Stir through some water with the baby leaves if needed!

• Divide coconut prawn and lentil dhal between bowls.
• Top with Greek-style yoghurt and tear over coriander. Serve with chilli flatbreads. Enjoy!